David Eppstein - Publications David Eppstein - Publications Ten algorithms for Egyptian fractions. D. Eppstein. Mathematica in Education and Research 4 (2): 5–15, 1995. Number theory. I survey and implement in Mathematica several methods for representing rational numbers as sums of distinct unit fractions. One of the methods involves searching for paths in a certain graph using a k shortest paths heuristic. (BibTeX – Citations – Also available in HTML and Mathematica notebook formats) Publications – David Eppstein – Theory Group – Inf. & Comp. Sci. – UC Irvine Semi-automatically filtered from a common source file.